OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F314A1779494576
OL,3,CUK scientists developing Ebola vaccine
OL,4,Cas outbreak spreads 'rapidly' in Congo
OL,6,FThe WHO chief Ghebreyesus noted that
OL,7,F82 cases have been confirmed in the
OL,8,FDemocratic Republic of Congo, with
OL,9,Fseven confirmed deaths, "but we know
OL,10,Fthe epidemic in DRC is much larger".
OL,12,FHe said there are now almost 750
OL,13,Fsuspected cases and 177 suspected
OL,14,Fdeaths.
OL,16,FThe situation in neighbouring Uganda
OL,17,Fis "stable" with two cases confirmed
OL,18,Fin people who had travelled from
OL,19,FCongo, with one death.
OL,26,@qD@YOUrD@cO]yD@DOUyD@KO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
