OL,3,CUK scientists developing Ebola vaccine
OL,4,Cas outbreak spreads 'rapidly' in Congo
OL,6,FThe outbreak is of a rare type of
OL,7,FEbola, known as the Bundibugyo virus
OL,8,Fand spread undetected for weeks
OL,9,Ffollowing the first known death, while
OL,10,Fauthorities tested for another, more
OL,11,Fcommon Ebola virus and came up
OL,12,Fnegative.
OL,14,FEbola itself is a rare, highly
OL,15,Fcontagious and often fatal disease
OL,16,Fgenerally transmitted via bodily
OL,17,Ffluids.
OL,19,FSymptoms include a high temperature,
OL,20,Fextreme tiredness, vomiting,
OL,21,Fdiarrhoea, muscle pain and bleeding.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
